Job Title: Senior Analytics Insights Engineer - Power BI
Ad Text:
We’re seeking a Senior Analytics Insights Engineer to join our clients team and help transform how data shapes decision-making across the business. This is a chance to work at the intersection of data, strategy, and operations, building solutions that create real value and partnering with stakeholders to deliver insights that make a measurable difference.

This role will be ideal for an experienced Data professional who has strong insights delivery experience (Power BI) and is comfortable modelling data and working with the latest data platforms.
  
Key responsibilities of the role:

Shape the way the business understands performance by building clear, insightful dashboards and reports.
Develop fit-for-purpose data models that make complex information simple and actionable.
Design and develop the silver and gold data layers for reporting 
Harness the power of Microsoft Fabric tools (lakehouses, warehouses, pipelines) and Power BI to deliver smarter, faster analytics solutions.
Translate raw data into meaningful stories and recommendations that support key decisions.
Partner with leaders across different business units to identify challenges, uncover opportunities, and embed analytics into everyday decision-making.
Contribute to a culture of agility and continuous improvement by championing data-driven approaches.
Drive innovation by using analytics to improve processes, enhance performance, and shape strategic initiatives.
  
Your skillset will include:

5 years of experience in insights/analytics, with a track record of delivering solutions in dynamic or complex organisations.
Strong skills in SQL and confidence working with large datasets and models.
Proven experience with Power BI to design and deliver engaging, business-ready dashboards.
Experience with Microsoft Fabric or similar data platforms, plus exposure to Azure or AWS cloud environments.
Python exposure is highly regarded
Comfortable working across multiple business areas and translating technical detail into clear business insights.
A degree in commerce, IT, mathematics, or engineering (or equivalent experience).
To be considered for this role, you must be an Australian Citizen or Permanent Resident.
  
If this position is of interest to you, please click ‘Apply’, or you can just send your details to raed@konnexuscg.com.au
Konnexus specialises in the recruitment of permanent and contract professionals within data analytics, AI/ML, data, and platform engineering. About EVT
When you join EVT, you are joining one of Australia and New Zealand’s leading experience companies. EVT encompasses Entertainment businesses that excite every sense, Ventures driven by a passion for new opportunities and Travel businesses that always feel local and authentic. At EVT, we’re the shakers and the Daymakers. The experience creators. The possibility makers and opportunity takers. We aim to make a positive impact on our people, communities and environment, every day.




Our Vision is being leaders in creating experiences and properties that escape the ordinary. 


Our Purpose is to make the day better for ourselves, each other, our group, our customers and communities. We do this by living our values of empowerment, possibilities and community. We achieve our Vision and Purpose by delivering on our goals and values.




Our Goals

Growing revenue above market 
Maximise assets 
Business transformation    




Our Values 

Empowerment: We make it happen
Possibilities: We evolve and innovate
Team Spirit: We make the connection







Position Overview

It’s an exciting time to join EVT as we continue to evolve how data and insights shape strategy and unlock business growth. As Lead Data Scientist, you’ll have a critical, high-impact role driving insights at the intersection of strategy, analytics, and commercial execution. The role is a strategic storyteller, translating EVT’s priorities into sharp analytical questions, then turning complex models into clear, concise, executive-ready narratives and actionable recommendations that drive decisions at SLT and Board level. 




With visibility across everything from pricing and marketing to venue operations and board-level planning, your insights will directly inform key decisions and strategic direction. You’ll help shape a data-driven culture in a high-energy environment that values both technical excellence and creative thinking, working with leading brands across entertainment, hotels and travel. If you're looking for a role where your work influences real outcomes and where your contributions are seen and felt across the organisation then this is it!




Responsibilities

Translate EVT priorities into analytical questions and executive-ready narratives for SLT and Board, with options, trade-offs, risks, and expected impact. 
Set the decision-science roadmap (segmentation, propensity/churn, CLV, demand forecasting, optimisation, experimentation). 
Develop and deploy advanced analytics models using tools such as SQL, Python, and machine learning techniques to solve key commercial challenges.
Drive the evolution of our customer strategy, building customer segmentation, propensity and churn models that enable more targeted marketing and richer customer experiences across the business.
Build and implement data-driven strategies that strengthen customer engagement, loyalty, and retention across both digital and in-venue channels.
Translate complex datasets into clear, actionable insights and communicate these effectively through data driven storytelling to senior leaders and non-technical stakeholders.
Drive pricing strategy, yield optimisation, and commercial modelling across venues and experiences to maximise profitability and customer value.
Champion test-and-learn practices through A/B testing, experimentation frameworks, and continuous optimisation of pricing, promotional, and customer engagement strategies.
Build and maintain predictive and prescriptive models to forecast demand, customer behaviour, and revenue opportunities.
Support strategic planning by embedding data into long-term forecasting, scenario analysis, and business case development.
Identify new data sources or external signals that could unlock value and inform strategic choices.
Partner with digital and technology teams to ensure data infrastructure supports scalable, efficient insight generation.


Experience

10+ years of experience in data analytics, data science, or commercial insights - preferably in consumer-facing sectors.
Proven ability to develop and activate customer segmentation frameworks that drive personalisation, improve marketing ROI, and deepen customer loyalty.
Deep technical proficiency in SQL and Python, with hands-on experience applying machine learning, clustering, regression, time series forecasting, etc.
Strong business acumen - demonstrated ability to influence strategic decisions and deliver tangible commercial outcomes.
Highly skilled in data storytelling - you bring numbers to life and influence with clarity and confidence.
Demonstrated success in developing and implementing pricing or yield strategies with measurable impact is a plus.
Comfortable working in ambiguity and evolving environments - you’re a proactive problem solver who thrives on complexity.
Experience working with BI tools (e.g. Power BI, Tableau, Looker) and data platforms (e.g. Snowflake, Redshift, Databricks).
A passion for building data-led customer strategies that balance commercial performance with meaningful audience connection.




Benefits & perks

At EVT, we want our people to experience our businesses and be brand and experience advocates. So, we make sure access to amazing ‘Elevate Perks’ are available to all staff from day dot. 

Incredible team member discounts from your first day on-the-job.  
50% off stays at EVT hotels – Rydges, LyLo, QT, Atura, and more.  
$2 movie tickets, plus Moonlight, Gold Class, Candy Bar discounts and more. 
Awesome winter and summer savings and discounts at Thredbo.  
Rapid career growth opportunities through our EVT network.  
Local community involvement, volunteering, and charitable giving.   
Australia and NZ’s largest and most diverse experiences company.

As the essential partner for transportation and critical infrastructure projects, complex non-residential construction and outdoor living solutions, CRH’s unique offering of materials, products and value-added services helps to deliver a more resilient and sustainable built environment. Ad Text:
About the role

Our Commonwealth Government client is seeking an APS6 Senior Data Analyst to interpret complex datasets and deliver insights that support strategic decision-making and organisational outcomes. The successful candidates will contribute to data quality initiatives, assess customer data requirements, and analyse matching scenarios using data management tools.

An initial 6-month labour hire contract is on offer. We anticipate a start date in early-November 2025.

This role is based in Adelaide; however other locations around Australia will be considered. Flexible working arrangements will also be considered.

Please note: only Australian citizens can be considered for this role.

Duties
Execute and oversee technical data tasks, including loading, maintaining, analysing, and distributing data.
Support data processing, matching, and management of master data elements.
Audit and enhance data quality through targeted programmes and error handling.
Resolve data integration issues and ensure alignment with enterprise systems and business needs.
Develop and maintain data standards, business rules, and retention criteria; contribute to governance strategy.
Provide data modelling support, ensuring documentation accuracy and consistency.
Collaborate with stakeholders to resolve issues, implement improvements, and support project delivery.
Lead a small team, managing priorities, performance, wellbeing, and capability development.

Requisite skills, experience, and knowledge
Demonstrated strategic thinking and ability to assess impacts across work areas.
Proven experience supervising and developing staff through coaching and mentoring.
Skilled in building and maintaining effective stakeholder relationships.
Strong risk identification, mitigation, and conflict management skills.
Effective at prioritising tasks and collaborating for quality outcomes.
Excellent communication skills, adaptable to different audiences.
Strong analytical skills with the ability to draw evidence-based conclusions.
Sound judgement in decision-making and problem-solving.

Required SFIA (Skills for the Information Age) levels:
Data modelling and design DTAN - Level 4
Programming/software development PROG - Level 2
Business intelligence BINT - Level 2
Data visualisation VISL - Level 3

Culture and benefits
People enjoy contracting with relatbl because our business is owned and managed by people who have first-hand experience working as contractors. We can relate. We treat people the way we would want to be treated, and we provide a range of perks and benefits to our staff.

How to apply
Click APPLY or get in touch with Fern (fern.boulton@relatbl.com.au) or Sam (sam.gavan@relatbl.com.au) for a confidential discussion. Applications for this position close on Sunday 12 October 2025. However, applications received after the closing date will be considered for similar future roles.

Ad Text:

Deep data expertise in SAP sales, procurement, and inventory

Experience in market-leading data solution tools to manage the end-to-end data life cycle including integration, storage, transformation, modelling, analysis and presentation.

Why work for us?

Ad Text:
Job description:


Are you looking for a new challenge and want to see your work make a real impact?
Gain skills with Australia's largest provider of government-funded hearing care
Permanent, Hybrid working, Macquarie Park based

Want to improve the lives of Australians, no matter who they are?

Join us and build a career and future you'll be proud of.

It matters more at Hearing Australia

Hearing Australia is a trusted leader in our field. Working across the country, we exist to support and empower people through hearing health when and where they need it.

Your opportunity

As a Senior Data Platform Engineer, you'll be reporting to the Data Engineering Manager, and will be responsible for the design, build and maintaining the Azure modern data platform. Lift data quality and governance. Keep the platform reliable, secure, and cost‑aware. Work with Microsoft Dynamics 365 and Clinical teams on clean upstream data. Working side by side with people who go the extra mile, you'll also love the feeling of helping children and adults who need us.

Must haves

Clear communication style. Able to explain complex data and architecture concepts to business stakeholders.
Minimum eight years of hands-on data engineering experience delivering enterprise-grade data solutions.
Architecture and operations mindset. Defines target patterns and reference designs, leads design reviews, sets up robust monitoring and alerting and manages incidents and problems effectively.
Designs solutions with security, privacy and reliability built in from the start.
Data governance expertise applied daily. Implements and maintains data quality checks, cataloguing, lineage tracking, glossary management and fine-grained access control using Microsoft Purview or equivalent tools.
Proven experience with Dynamics 365 and Dataverse.
Proven delivery of modern data warehouse platforms in production environments, including design, build, deployment and ongoing maintenance for performance and reliability.
Deep Azure platform expertise across Azure Data Lake Storage (Gen2), Azure Databricks, Azure Synapse Analytics, Microsoft Fabric and Azure Data Factory, with supporting experience in Azure Functions, Logic Apps, Event Hubs or Stream Analytics.
Strong data modelling experience. Designs and maintains star schemas, lakehouse layers and semantic models in Microsoft Fabric or Power BI.
Expert-level SQL skills with proficiency in either Python or PySpark.
CI/CD for data pipelines using Azure DevOps. Builds and maintains automated deployment pipelines with structured branching strategies, environment promotion, approval workflows, and release automation for data assets and infrastructure.

Nice to haves

Advanced Microsoft Fabric capabilities and complex pipeline orchestration
Strong FinOps awareness, including cost monitoring and optimisation.
Experience supporting data science and AI initiatives, ML-ready datasets or Azure Machine Learning integration

Why Hearing Australia?

There's so much to love about a role with us. But our people say there's three things that set us and their careers apart. They're about:

How we do what we do: Our vision is to deliver the best hearing solutions for anyone, anytime, anywhere. At Hearing Australia, you'll know you're making a contribution that really means something
Who we work with: Here, you'll support and empower clients of all backgrounds. That's what drives our teams and what makes them so special
Where we're going next: As our industry evolves, we're committed to learning and improving what we do and how we do it and building an organisation where everyone can thrive.

What does that mean for you?

As a Senior Data Platform Engineer you'll know that every day, your work is helping children and adults who need us. Just ask Sandeep, one of our IT professionals about why they choose to work with us:

"The work we do in helping people hear sound again and for the very first time is quite inspirational. Everything we do here is purpose-driven."

You'll also enjoy a range of benefits, including:

Attractive employee benefits (salary sacrifice superannuation, HCF private health cover discount, well-being programs, salary packaging, discounts across an exciting range of retailers)
Free, onsite staff parking
Employee recognition awards programFlexible work arrangement opportunities to support work, personal and family commitments
Flexible work arrangement opportunities to support work, personal and family commitments

Let's create the gold standard of hearing care

We will require the successful candidate to be willing to have a Police Check conducted (we pay), a current driver's licence and must have rights to work in Australia.

Hearing Australia is an Equal Opportunity Employer and embraces diversity, equity and inclusion. We are passionate about building a diverse and inclusive culture from within.

We encourage Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples and applicants from different cultures who are bilingual to apply.

We are committed to facilitating a barrier-free recruitment process and work environment. If you require any accommodations, we welcome you to let us know so we can work with you to participate fully in our recruitment experience.

As a Senior CIRT (Cyber Incident Response Team) Analyst, you will play a critical hands-on role within the Cyber Defence team, responsible for leading complex incident investigations, building and tuning threat detection capabilities, and mentoring SOC Analysts to support global 24/7 operations. In this role, you will act as the primary escalation point for incidents that exceed Tier 1/2 capabilities and ensures operational continuity outside of Security Operations leadership working hours. Lead incident response lifecycle from detection through to post-incident review.
Perform high level forensic analysis across cloud, endpoint and network data.
Develop and execute hypothesis driven hunts across available telemetry.
Use results to identify gaps or refine detection logic.

Support the development of SOC Analysts by providing escalation support, training and structured feedback.

Experience building detection logic and analytics rules (e.g. KQL, Sigma)

Experience in financial services, aviation, government or other regulated industries

Experience with Sentinel, Defender and CrowdStrike

Hello. We’re Virgin Australia.

We’re the airline that’s always done things a little different. Our way. The Virgin way.

We’re on a mission to make flying better than ‘nice’. And to do that, it takes a team of talented people who are passionate about customer experience, doing the right thing always, with a focus on safety – in the air, on the ground and in our workplaces. A team who values real diversity and inclusion, in a big brand with big ambitions.

What you’ll be doing

This role sits within our Revenue Management team and reports to the Senior Manager, Ancillary Product & Strategy. You’ll be part of a team that’s shaping the future of our product portfolio – from strategy and performance reporting to proposition evolution and BAU product management.

You’ll work across the business to support the development of our 3-year product strategy and roadmap, dive deep into data to uncover insights, and help bring new ideas to life. You’ll also get to see the impact of your work every time you fly with us – because what you do will help make our guests’ experience even better.

You’ll be great in this role if you…

You’re a strategic thinker with a knack for turning data into stories that drive decisions. You’ve got experience in strategy, consulting or commercial analytics, and you’re comfortable working with ambiguity. You know your way around Excel and PowerBI, and you’re confident communicating with stakeholders at all levels.

You’re curious, collaborative, and love solving problems. You’re not afraid to challenge the status quo and bring fresh ideas to the table. And you care about doing things the right way – with integrity, attention to detail, and a focus on impact.

2+ years’ experience in strategy/management consulting or similar commercial analytics roles
Strong skills in data analysis, insight generation, and stakeholder communication
Advanced Excel and PowerBI (or similar tools)

We’re committed to looking after you, with some of the best benefits and conditions in the industry – including (but not limited to):

Discounted flights for you and your loved ones (including $1000 worth of travel credits per year)
A flexible, hybrid work style. Work from home or the office, adapt your location to suit your style and needs
One of Brisbane’s most admired head office locations, with South Bank train station, a supermarket, pharmacy, and lunch options downstairs plus a 5-minute walk to the Busway, a rooftop restaurant and onsite gym (with a low membership fee) and South Bank Parklands just across the road
Discounts on travel insurance, lounge membership, car hire, accommodation, and experiences worldwide
Cheaper hospitality, retail, technology, beauty and wellness services
Free counselling and access to a wellbeing app to support your physical, mental, social and financial health
‘Dress for Your Day’ – enjoy the freedom to wear whatever makes you feel great for the type of work you do and the day you have ahead of you.

When everyone is included, everyone wins

We’re all individuals. And we love that. That’s why we encourage applications from Indigenous Australians, people with disability, those from diverse cultural backgrounds, our friends in the LGBTQI+ community, and anyone else who wants to join our family.
